Description: CVE-2026-49218 - Added missing check for returning an image with zero columns or rows
 ImageMagick's DCM (DICOM) decoder in ReadDCMImage was missing a check
 for zero rows or columns. A crafted DICOM file with Rows=0 and/or
 Columns=0 produced a zero-dimension Image* that could cause denial of
 service in downstream operations. This patch adds a guard that returns
 a CorruptImageError ImproperImageHeader when the decoded image has
 zero rows or columns.
 .
 Tracked as GHSA-8pj9-6897-74xc.
