Description: CVE-2026-56361 - fix off-by-one out-of-bounds read in AcquireKernelBuiltIn
 An off-by-one error in the morphology kernel argument validation in
 AcquireKernelBuiltIn allowed args->xi and args->psi to equal
 kernel->width and kernel->height respectively, resulting in a
 single-pixel out-of-bounds heap read (CWE-125). The bounds checks are
 tightened from strict-greater-than (`>`) to greater-or-equal (`>=`) so
 values equal to the kernel dimension are now rejected.
 .
 This backport applies the upstream fix from ImageMagick6 commit
 cb02de6a5b527edc51982408ad719d76c6699d78 to the Debian bullseye
 6.9.11.60+dfsg-1.3+deb11u4 source. Only the two comparison lines are
 changed; the surrounding `(size_t)` casts in the Debian tree are left
 untouched (upstream had migrated to CastDoubleToSizeT() but that helper
 is not part of the security fix).
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/cb02de6a5b527edc51982408ad719d76c6699d78
Bug: https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/security/advisories/GHSA-q8h3-jv9v-57qx
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-07-03
--- a/magick/morphology.c
+++ b/magick/morphology.c
@@ -1569,8 +1569,8 @@
               return(DestroyKernelInfo(kernel));    /* invalid args given */
             kernel->width = (size_t)args->rho;
             kernel->height = (size_t)args->sigma;
-            if ( args->xi  < 0.0 || args->xi  > (double)kernel->width ||
-                 args->psi < 0.0 || args->psi > (double)kernel->height )
+            if ((args->xi < 0.0) || (args->xi  >= (double) kernel->width) ||
+                (args->psi < 0.0) || (args->psi >= (double) kernel->height))
               return(DestroyKernelInfo(kernel));    /* invalid args given */
             kernel->x = (ssize_t) args->xi;
             kernel->y = (ssize_t) args->psi;
